2 minute Strawberry Ice Cream

4 oz fresh strawberries hulled
1/2 c heavy cream
2/3 c superfine sugar (can use granulated, but blended for a minute to make fine)
3 tbsp lemon juice
18 oz frozen strawberries

Place the fresh strawberries, cream, sugar, and lemon juice in the blender in the order listed. Start low and grandually increase speed to blend until sugar is fully dissolved, ~ 45 s. Add frozen strawberries, again start on low speed gradually increasing and blend until ice cream is smooth, ~ 1min. Use tamper as needed to stir the ice cream mixture and push it down. Can serve immediately or freeze for later (will be firmer from freezer)
